  "prompt": "I can't remember the combination on my carlton suitcase, how do I 'crack' it?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you've forgotten your combination on your Carlton suitcase! Before trying to 'crack' the combination lock, here are a few steps to consider:\n\n1. **Check Documentation**: Sometimes the original combination may be documented in paperwork that came with the suitcase when you purchased it.\n\n2. **Default Codes**: Many suitcase locks come with preset default codes such as 000 or 123. Try these if you can't remember a personal combination.\n\n3. **Contact Customer Support**: Carlton customer service may be able to provide specific advice or instructions for your model. They may have procedures in place to verify ownership before helping unlock the suitcase.\n\n4. **Using Trial and Error**: If none of the above methods work, you might need to try every combination manually, which could be time-consuming. If your lock has three dials, there are 1,000 possible combinations (from 000 to 999).\n\n5. **Professional Locksmith**: If you can't unlock it yourself, a professional locksmith might be able to help without damaging the suitcase.\n\nAttempting to forcibly open or 'crack' the suitcase lock could damage it, and it\u2019s recommended to use these above methods. If the situation is urgent, a locksmith is usually the safest option.",
